  "target_response": {
    "text": "It shows up, and more clearly than app guilt would: across 12 tagged drinking days versus 45 comparison days, your next-day recovery ran about 7 points lower on average — one of the stronger patterns in your log, graded medium confidence. The usual caveats still apply. This is a correlation: weekend drinks travel with later nights and later meals, and the data can't fully separate those companions from the alcohol itself. But 12 tagged days is a reasonable sample, and the direction is consistent with how alcohol typically shows up in overnight heart measures. If you want to size the real effect, run your own comparison: a couple of weekends with drinks at your normal time but an unchanged bedtime. If recovery still dips, the drinks are carrying it; if it holds, the late nights were.",
